  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reducing Tuberculosis and HIV in Mining Communities of Southern Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To decrease Tuberculosis and associated risk factors by providing miners, ex-miners and their communities improved Tuberculosis diagnosis, treatment and follow-up. This will benefit a significant number of miners, their mining communities and labour sending communities and reduce the incidence and spread of this highly infectious disease. This contributes to our MDGs by halting and reversing the incidence of Tuberculosis in the mining sector and associated communities in Southern Africa by December 2016.</narrative>
  </description>
